<item>
            <title>[LU-13977] sanity test_255a uses integer comparison for non-integers</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13977</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The &quot;-gt&quot; option in the shell &quot;[&apos;&quot; (aka &quot;test&quot;) command compares integers.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;ladvise_willread_performance() in sanity.sh uses &quot;scale=2&quot; to ask bc to calculate values to 2 decimal places.&#160; These values are then compared with &quot;-gt&quot; which will fail (unless by luck they are integers).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This failure is not normally noticed as the error is only reported when no vm is detected.&#160; (When I run qemu, no vm is detected, so I notice.)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
